  "del:hasArgument": [
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_62b2405f-43f3-4cf3-bc93-197f5813b028",
      "del:text": "What card did you think needed to be turned ?"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_b94ecfe0-7836-494b-a2c6-bea271e2fb41",
      "del:text": "All right , so I was thinking just the last card <CARD>"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_d4322920-2af7-4eae-8c17-398ca6c20598",
      "del:text": "'that''s the one I chose'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_cca92b59-8bc7-4003-89e7-6c84d93aaef4",
      "del:text": "<MENTION> ?"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_de568861-45fd-4aaf-a79c-893a3ca7ca7e",
      "del:text": "I picked <CARD> and <CARD>"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_e59d5e32-ab26-4330-88dc-7a40e28ca4b0",
      "del:text": "'The rule is \" All cards with vowels on one side have an even number on the other \" ; we could check <CARD> but it wouldn''t tell us anything , because the rule doesn''t say what needs to be on the opposite side of even numbers ; just on the opposite side of Vowels .'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_8c4f378e-99d5-4912-8b77-5f11f9b0990b",
      "del:text": "'So if the opposite side of <CARD> was , say , a B , that wouldn''t say the rule is wrong . Because the rule just says IF there''s a vowel , THEN must have an even number on the back .'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_cff0cabe-cd02-4ee7-ac51-d996eddc401a",
      "del:text": "Not that there must also be vowels behind every even number ."
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_62fe05da-6a9f-4a55-9341-2384e77510f6",
      "del:text": "<CARD> should have a vowel on the back ."
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_ce3585dc-673c-43a6-a1ff-32ef42d69816",
      "del:text": "'My thinking was that if even numbers are behind the vowels it could be that the oppisite is also true . There is no way to tell of course but it''s is worth thinking about'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_66fe563a-f926-4104-9084-793d25a8dc52",
      "del:text": "'I''m going with <CARD>'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_b94d778e-c5c0-48b2-b1ea-251642dc8173",
      "del:text": "<CARD> can have a vowel on the back , but it could also have a consonant . The rule is \" All cards with vowels on one side have an even number on the other \" . Does not say anything about \" all cards with evens \""
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_5d0e9743-95bd-4fe5-be75-9d71c197d0c0",
      "del:text": "I gottcha"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_ea577588-e91f-4eca-84a0-ddcd523d9af5",
      "del:text": "true but the rule can still suggest the reverse"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_59a9af0f-0c9b-4a68-9697-f85639637c33",
      "del:text": "It would be a very good indication , yes , but it could not actually test the rule"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_f781f6aa-7fa2-4161-9c7d-c685fe8986c0",
      "del:text": "End the end none of us can be sure"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_f42a2909-cfb1-41d3-9234-8f96dda4b8ce",
      "del:text": "'I''m ready with my final answer how about everyone else ?'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_d8c34663-c5ab-4f18-909c-e313b463817d",
      "del:text": "I am as well"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_1033da65-986a-415e-84c7-f6e7aad30294",
      "del:text": "'We need to pick one that wouldn''t fit the rule to test it . Maybe ?'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_95a91c27-1dc0-4d59-aacc-6608d1dd10f4",
      "del:text": "'I just realized that if we choose <CARD> or <CARD> , and it''s a vowel on the back , that breaks the rule'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_43c1a604-482f-42f9-a7eb-e93c27144c12",
      "del:text": "TRUE"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_5b2f7eba-4944-408d-98b9-bf3c4cd6a4cb",
      "del:text": "Yep , confirmation bias ."
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_a13fa9cb-8e9f-4765-a360-e26ea2a3fe65",
      "del:text": "'I''m still sure <CARD> won''t tell us anything but the other checks will'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_62be5e31-c8f6-49de-ad19-c6c17c3d06c2",
      "del:text": "<CARD> and <CARD> ?"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_5b8c5459-67a2-4cea-b76b-f830ecbce7c9",
      "del:text": "yeah same so I think that means we should end it"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_d868c641-e9c5-4e7e-a7f9-8e2976e9b0ca",
      "del:text": "<CARD> <CARD> and <CARD> is what I chose"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_1f190998-f7ec-459a-9065-4b86e5f3bb96",
      "del:text": "everything but <CARD>"
    }
  ]
